The paper proposes a novel network architecture for sketch recognition, which involves both RNN and CNN. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of attention mechanism and end-to-end learning also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the conversion of vector sketches into bitmap images, which may be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper focuses on recognizing sketches drawn by humans, which may be relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
